The Kubernetes Crusade: Workshop on Defending & Attacking Kubernetes

Preparing the Environment for Lab Setup

Setup the Prerequisite

  • Move the course content required for this training to the current directory and ensure its visibility on the left pane.
cp -r /home/ubuntu/course .

  • Change the directory to the course and list its contents to verify the presence of the required labs.
cd course/
ls

Below example is an indicative output & continues to update as new lessons are incorporated.

  • Execute the "cat" command to read the contents of the Kubernetes cluster setup script. This script will be used to set up the prerequisites for the Kubernetes cluster.
cat k8s-setup.sh

  • Execute the Bash script to pre-setup the required components for the cluster.
bash k8s-setup.sh

  • Run apt update to update the packages.
sudo apt update

if apt-update is failing, run below command to add the key.gpg and update the sources .

curl -sSL https://packages.cloud.google.com/apt/doc/apt-key.gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/kubernetes-archive-keyring.gpg

echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/kubernetes-archive-keyring.gpg] https://apt.kubernetes.io/ kubernetes-xenial main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/kubernetes.list

Troubleshooting

  • In case of ubuntu stops responding, please run below comman

Clear Cache in Linux

 sync; echo 1 > /proc/sys/vm/drop_caches
 sync; echo 2 > /proc/sys/vm/drop_caches
 sync; echo 3 > /proc/sys/vm/drop_caches
